race.comment: Competitive. BLACK PEPPERMINT (2) made significant late ground last start to get up for third over 2200m at Sale. Built on his 1.5L defeat at Kilmore and peaks for a smart yard. All set to win in country grade. AUTUMNHEAT (1) rates a danger. Progressed nicely last start to finish a close second over 2400m at Bendigo. Drops back 2000m but will be hitting the line hard. STAR TESTYMONY (5) was quickly up to a middle distance, narrowly missing at Warrnambool. Has a wide gate to contend with, but is sure to keep improving. LARSEN BAY (7) rates similarly on his spacious 56 win at Kilmore. Races forward and has weight relief at this level. That brings her into it. DIGARI (8) has been racing well without winning and can't be ruled out.
